==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insoul
<hw>In*soul"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To set a soul in;
reflexively, to fix one's strongest affections on.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] could not but <qex>insoul</qex> himself in her.</q>
<rj><qau>Feltham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inspan</ent>⟦br⟧
